        <Node ToolID="100">
          <GuiSettings Plugin="AlteryxGuiToolkit.TextBox.TextBox">
            <Position x="632" y="642" width="1020" height="336" />
          </GuiSettings>
          <Properties>
            <Configuration>
              <Text>- Use the Report Map tool to create a thematic map. Specify the Purchase sum as the column to do a thematic map on. Within the Thematic Tab, Equal Count is selected as the Tile method because it produces a more interesting map. A range of green is chosen to reflect the purchase value of each ZIP Code.

- Use the Report Text tool is configured to add a title to the map.

- Use the Map Legend Splitter macro to extract all the elements of the legend into separate columns.

- Use the Formala tool to add a $ symbols to the front of the 'ThemeBandFrom' and 'ThemeBandTo' columns and these columns are then used to build up the text for the 'Text' column.

- Use the Map Legend Builder macro to rebuild the legend.

- Use the Report Text tool to add a title to the legend.

- Use the Append Fields tool to bring together the map and the legend columns.

- Use the Layout tool to align the map and legend together vertically.

- Use the Report Header macro to add a header column to the row.

- Use the Report Footer macro to add a footer column to the row.

- Use the Render tool to render the map to a PDF. After the workflow is run, view the PDF containing the map by clicking on the hyperlink in the Results Window.</Text>
              <Font name="Segoe UI" size="8.25" style="0" />
              <TextColor name="Black" />
              <FillColor name="White" />
              <Shape shape="3" />
              <Justification Justification="0" />
            </Configuration>
            <Annotation DisplayMode="0">
              <Name />
              <DefaultAnnotationText />
              <Left value="False" />
            </Annotation>
          </Properties>
        </Node>
      </ChildNodes>
    </Node>
